17ConnectionStyle::ConnectionStyle()
18{
19 // Explicit resources inialization for preventing the static initialization
20 // order fiasco: https://isocpp.org/wiki/faq/ctors#static-init-order
21 initResources();
22 // This configuration is stored inside the compiled unit and is loaded
23 // statically
24 loadJsonFile(":DefaultStyle.json");
25}
26ConnectionStyle::ConnectionStyle(QString jsonText)
27{
28 loadJsonFile(":DefaultStyle.json");
29 loadJsonText(jsonText);
30}
31void ConnectionStyle::setConnectionStyle(QString jsonText)
32{
33 ConnectionStyle style(jsonText);
34 StyleCollection::setConnectionStyle(style);
35}
36#ifdef STYLE_DEBUG
37 #define CONNECTION_STYLE_CHECK_UNDEFINED_VALUE(v, variable) \
38 { \
39 if (v.type() == QJsonValue::Undefined || v.type() == QJsonValue::Null) \
40 qWarning() << "Undefined value for parameter:" << #variable; \
41 }
42#else
43 #define CONNECTION_STYLE_CHECK_UNDEFINED_VALUE(v, variable)
44#endif
45#define CONNECTION_VALUE_EXISTS(v) (v.type() != QJsonValue::Undefined && v.type() != QJsonValue::Null)
46#define CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(values, variable) \
47 { \
48 auto valueRef = values[#variable]; \
49 CONNECTION_STYLE_CHECK_UNDEFINED_VALUE(valueRef, variable) \
50 if (CONNECTION_VALUE_EXISTS(valueRef)) \
51 { \
52 if (valueRef.isArray()) \
53 { \
54 auto colorArray = valueRef.toArray(); \
55 std::vector<int> rgb; \
56 rgb.reserve(3); \
57 for (auto it = colorArray.begin(); it != colorArray.end(); ++it) \
58 { \
59 rgb.push_back((*it).toInt()); \
60 } \
61 variable = QColor(rgb[0], rgb[1], rgb[2]); \
62 } \
63 else \
64 { \
65 variable = QColor(valueRef.toString()); \
66 } \
67 } \
68 }
69#define CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_FLOAT(values, variable) \
70 { \
71 auto valueRef = values[#variable]; \
72 CONNECTION_STYLE_CHECK_UNDEFINED_VALUE(valueRef, variable) \
73 if (CONNECTION_VALUE_EXISTS(valueRef)) \
74 variable = valueRef.toDouble(); \
75 }
76#define CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_BOOL(values, variable) \
77 { \
78 auto valueRef = values[#variable]; \
79 CONNECTION_STYLE_CHECK_UNDEFINED_VALUE(valueRef, variable) \
80 if (CONNECTION_VALUE_EXISTS(valueRef)) \
81 variable = valueRef.toBool(); \
82 }
83void ConnectionStyle::loadJsonFile(QString styleFile)
84{
85 QFile file(styleFile);
86 if (!file.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly))
87 {
88 qWarning() << "Couldn't open file " << styleFile;
89 return;
90 }
91 loadJsonFromByteArray(file.readAll());
92}
93void ConnectionStyle::loadJsonText(QString jsonText)
94{
95 loadJsonFromByteArray(jsonText.toUtf8());
96}
97void ConnectionStyle::loadJsonFromByteArray(QByteArray const &byteArray)
98{
99 QJsonDocument json(QJsonDocument::fromJson(byteArray));
100 QJsonObject topLevelObject = json.object();
101 QJsonValueRef nodeStyleValues = topLevelObject["ConnectionStyle"];
102 QJsonObject obj = nodeStyleValues.toObject();
103 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(obj, ConstructionColor);
104 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(obj, NormalColor);
105 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(obj, SelectedColor);
106 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(obj, SelectedHaloColor);
107 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_COLOR(obj, HoveredColor);
108 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_FLOAT(obj, LineWidth);
109 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_FLOAT(obj, ConstructionLineWidth);
110 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_FLOAT(obj, PointDiameter);
111 CONNECTION_STYLE_READ_BOOL(obj, UseDataDefinedColors);
112}
113QColor ConnectionStyle::constructionColor() const
114{
115 return ConstructionColor;
116}
117QColor ConnectionStyle::normalColor() const
118{
119 return NormalColor;
120}
121QColor ConnectionStyle::normalColor(QString typeId) const
122{
123 std::size_t hash = qHash(typeId);
124 std::size_t const hue_range = 0xFF;
125 std::srand(hash);
126 std::size_t hue = std::rand() % hue_range;
127 std::size_t sat = 120 + hash % 129;
128 return QColor::fromHsl(hue, sat, 160);
129}
